Good to see you, %PLAYERNAME%! Question—have you been by the woods at all lately?
I ask because a nearby forest has been looking pretty lush lately.
It reminded me of some old stories I came across back in my student days.
There are accounts from different eras that describe trees flourishing in the forest along with the appearance of a particular Pokémon.
I wonder if any of those tales are true. I’ll have to dig into my notes and find the name of the Pokémon they’re referring to.
Welcome back! Have you had a chance to observe any of the surrounding locations?
Whenever I find myself getting lost in my notes, I like to take breaks near trees in the area.
Oh, speaking of my notes—the Pokémon in the stories I was talking about earlier turns out to have been Celebi!
And—this is the really juicy part—Celebi is known as the Time Travel Pokémon. It came here from the future by crossing over time!
Sounds right out of a myth, right? Let’s keep investigating and see if the phenomenon I observed is connected to Celebi!
%PLAYERNAME%! I was just looking for you! Did you turn up anything interesting in your own investigation?
I actually think I spotted Celebi in the wild!
It seemed like it was bolstering the grass and trees around it—and that matches what’s recorded about it.
Its coloring was different than expected, though. What could that mean?
Whatever the answer, we ought to keep an eye out for our fantastical forest friend.
I’ve been looking inward a lot lately—meditative, even. I wonder if it’s due to Celebi’s presence?
They say that it only appears during peaceful times...
Well, if that’s true, I hope it stays with us for a long time!
How about you, %PLAYERNAME%? Have you felt inspired by the calm?
It might be nice to spend some time basking in the serenity around us with your buddy!
I saw Celebi again! It flew off when I tried to approach, but I found an egg near where I spotted it.
According to my research, Celebi is said to leave behind an egg it brought from the future, so I can’t wait to study this one!
This is a good sign! We’re going to have another encounter with Celebi—I can just feel it!
You keep up the good work exploring—and make sure you’re prepared for when the time comes.
It’s no small feat to catch a Mythical Pokémon like Celebi, but I’m sure you have what it takes!
Yes! You’ve done brilliantly, %PLAYERNAME%! I’m so proud of you for seeing this task through.
And what a worthwhile task it was! Just look at the hue on your new friend there—this is a Shiny Celebi!
It’s thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.
And if you ask me, your contribution towards that future will be nothing short of mythical!
Make sure to take some time to celebrate with your new friend, Trainer. And until next time, let’s GO!

“Life force,” Professor Willow says? Peculiar. I wonder—would those flames transform if Litwick were to evolve?
Perfect timing, %PLAYERNAME%! I’ve got an electrifying adventure lined up for you today.
I’ve been monitoring some nearby waters and have picked up intriguing electrical signals.
If my hunch is correct, we’ve got a school of the Electric-type Pokémon Tynamo on our hands! Well, maybe not literally on our hands—they’re pretty zappy—but you know what I mean.
See if you can spot any Tynamo out there. Even better if you can bring one back for us to study up close!
Welcome back, %PLAYERNAME%. I see I was right to charge you with researching Tynamo today!
I just learned that one Tynamo alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.
And things get even more shocking once Tynamo evolves!
Why don’t you try evolving your Tynamo into Eelektrik so we can study it together?
Incredible work, %PLAYERNAME%. Your Eelektrik has me en-wrap-tured! Get it? Because they coil around their prey!
Anyway... If you look closely, you can see these circular patterns along Eelektrik’s body are actually electricity-generating organs.
That’s why I always pack a pair of rubber gloves. You never know when you’ll be handling Electric-type Pokémon.
Now, I think you’re ready to take this research up a notch and evolve your Eelektrik into Eelektross!
Wow! What an achievement, %PLAYERNAME%. Your Eelektross has me totally amped!
Did you know that Eelektross’ fangs have electricity running through them? It makes me glad I didn’t become a Pokémon dentist! Haha.
The fact that you’ve befriended such a phenomenal Electric-type Pokémon is grounds for celebration, I say!
Keep up the fantastic work out there. I’m sure I’ll see you again soon. Until then, let’s GO!
